00:24:32.750 --> 00:24:37.396
The third thing, is that right
now at the United Nations,

00:24:37.396 --> 00:24:39.270
there's a tremendously
important conversation

00:24:39.270 --> 00:24:42.910
taking place related to the
Millennium Development Goals.

00:24:42.910 --> 00:24:45.940
In the year 2000, the
international community

00:24:45.940 --> 00:24:48.506
came together to build sort
of the definitive roadmap

00:24:48.506 --> 00:24:51.130
for addressing poverty, and they
set out these eight Millennium

00:24:51.130 --> 00:24:52.241
Development Goals.

00:24:52.241 --> 00:24:54.490
And they've been pursuing
them over the last 15 years,

00:24:54.490 --> 00:24:57.270
and have seen some really
significant progress

00:24:57.270 --> 00:24:58.884
on those targeted things.

00:24:58.884 --> 00:25:01.050
The big problem that people
are starting to realize,

00:25:01.050 --> 00:25:04.440
though, is that they spoke
of the massive solution

00:25:04.440 --> 00:25:06.860
to try to deal with
poverty, and they did not

00:25:06.860 --> 00:25:09.130
say a word about violence.

00:25:09.130 --> 00:25:13.690
And now, imagine you're trying
to move the world forward out

00:25:13.690 --> 00:25:15.410
of poverty, but you're
not doing anything

00:25:15.410 --> 00:25:17.480
about this violence
that is just ripping

00:25:17.480 --> 00:25:20.330
the rug out from underneath
everyone's ability

00:25:20.330 --> 00:25:21.280
to move forward.

00:25:21.280 --> 00:25:23.350
So we have a petition that
we're putting together

00:25:23.350 --> 00:25:26.260
and there's a way to sign
on there that will just

00:25:26.260 --> 00:25:29.610
be going to the UN team that
is starting to put together

00:25:29.610 --> 00:25:32.430
the Millennium Development Goals
to say, hey, let's just make

00:25:32.430 --> 00:25:35.450
sure that this conversation
includes addressing

00:25:35.450 --> 00:25:38.740
the violence that is descending
like locusts upon the poor

00:25:38.740 --> 00:25:40.260
in developing world.

00:25:40.260 --> 00:25:43.930
This is, again, from the
AIDS epidemic perspective,

00:25:43.930 --> 00:25:45.870
it wasn't just the
public health experts.

00:25:45.870 --> 00:25:50.210
It wasn't just the sort
of global affairs experts

00:25:50.210 --> 00:25:52.330
that rang the alarm
about the problem,

00:25:52.330 --> 00:25:54.500
and said, no, this is
something we need to address.

00:25:54.500 --> 00:25:56.930
It was very, very
common people who

00:25:56.930 --> 00:26:00.390
began to think differently
about the problems in the world

00:26:00.390 --> 00:26:02.890
and to make sure that we were
addressing this epidemic as

00:26:02.890 --> 00:26:03.490
well.

00:26:03.490 --> 00:26:05.365
And I think it's an
opportunity for all of us

00:26:05.365 --> 00:26:07.260
to raise our voice
on behalf of those

00:26:07.260 --> 00:26:09.031
who are victims of
violence as well.

