does that decrease violence

00:26:52.720 --> 00:26:55.020
in those countries
that [INAUDIBLE]

00:26:55.020 --> 00:26:56.760
and by which factor?

00:26:56.760 --> 00:26:58.580
And two.

00:26:58.580 --> 00:27:00.600
This experiment that
you did in the city

00:27:00.600 --> 00:27:04.365
with the sex trafficking,
how much did it cost and can

00:27:04.365 --> 00:27:09.370
you put a price
[INAUDIBLE] on this program

00:27:09.370 --> 00:27:12.886
compared to if you had given
meals, and food, and whatever,

00:27:12.886 --> 00:27:15.200
what the benefits are.

00:27:15.200 --> 00:27:17.610
GARY A. HAUGEN:
Yeah, great question.

00:27:17.610 --> 00:27:21.910
Sort of going at the first one,
I mean, the second one first.

00:27:21.910 --> 00:27:26.970
The data on the actual
cost of law enforcement

00:27:26.970 --> 00:27:28.670
is available to us.

00:27:28.670 --> 00:27:30.580
It'll give you an idea
of what it would cost.

00:27:30.580 --> 00:27:36.350
The data is not very good about
how much the economic benefit

00:27:36.350 --> 00:27:37.950
is from all of that.

00:27:37.950 --> 00:27:40.105
And so it's just being
very much developed.

00:27:40.105 --> 00:27:42.370
But what you can
see, for instance,

00:27:42.370 --> 00:27:44.840
is that where the
studies have been done,

00:27:44.840 --> 00:27:50.650
the GDP is reduced
somewhere between 2% and 7%

00:27:50.650 --> 00:27:54.290
an entire nation by criminal
violence and violence

00:27:54.290 --> 00:27:55.339
in the community.

00:27:55.339 --> 00:27:57.880
You will see, in they did some
studies in Latin America where

00:27:57.880 --> 00:28:02.430
they showed half of the
accumulated net social capital

00:28:02.430 --> 00:28:07.060
was eliminated, half of it
over a 15-year period of time

00:28:07.060 --> 00:28:08.290
because of violence.

00:28:08.290 --> 00:28:10.080
They're starting
to begin to develop

00:28:10.080 --> 00:28:12.530
the numerical costs of violence.

00:28:12.530 --> 00:28:16.200
It costs for instance in what
they call Disability Adjusted

00:28:16.200 --> 00:28:21.820
Life Years, about 9 million
Disability Adjusted life years

00:28:21.820 --> 00:28:25.150
are wasted because of violence
against women and girls.

00:28:25.150 --> 00:28:28.060
And so that's massive
amounts of productivity.

00:28:28.060 --> 00:28:34.300
What you also know is that the
economies that are actually

00:28:34.300 --> 00:28:37.210
producing social mobility
are the ones that

00:28:37.210 --> 00:28:40.935
provide protection for
those who are poorest.

00:28:40.935 --> 00:28:42.560
Because in the absence
of that, they're

00:28:42.560 --> 00:28:45.392
unable to keep even the
benefits of their effort.

00:28:45.392 --> 00:28:47.600
Some of this is hard to see,
though, because in, as I

00:28:47.600 --> 00:28:50.545
explained a little bit, in
low income and middle income

00:28:50.545 --> 00:28:51.920
countries right
now, you actually

00:28:51.920 --> 00:28:57.940
see some significant rates of
economic growth, reasonable GDP

00:28:57.940 --> 00:28:58.600
advancements.

00:28:58.600 --> 00:29:01.930
But what you see when you
look at it, and disaggregate

00:29:01.930 --> 00:29:03.910
it is that that
economic growth is

00:29:03.910 --> 00:29:06.850
coming from the sector
of the country that

00:29:06.850 --> 00:29:09.960
has protected itself
with private security.

00:29:09.960 --> 00:29:13.170
And that's a massive
expense, by the way, that

00:29:13.170 --> 00:29:15.840
could be poured into a public
security, but at the moment

00:29:15.840 --> 00:29:18.780
is just privatizing part of it.

00:29:18.780 --> 00:29:22.380
One of things that the book does
is call for much greater study

00:29:22.380 --> 00:29:24.140
of how much would this cost?

00:29:24.140 --> 00:29:25.860
What would the benefit be?

00:29:25.860 --> 00:29:28.700
But there certainly is now
enough data from the World Bank

00:29:28.700 --> 00:29:31.990
and from other multilateral
institutions that

00:29:31.990 --> 00:29:35.660
suggest that what is lost
to violence is massive.

00:29:35.660 --> 00:29:39.150
And that if we don't get out in
front of it, that kind of cost

00:29:39.150 --> 00:29:40.860
is just going to grow.

00:29:40.860 --> 00:29:42.430
Yeah.

