00:36:53.120 --> 00:36:55.470
And to be clear,
you can see why this

00:36:55.470 --> 00:36:57.670
is why crime runs to
those places, right?

00:36:57.670 --> 00:36:59.910
It runs to be amongst
the poor, because they're

00:36:59.910 --> 00:37:02.590
going to be the least empowered.

00:37:02.590 --> 00:37:04.050
One of things we
do, of course, is

00:37:04.050 --> 00:37:08.110
take that kind of technology
into those communities

00:37:08.110 --> 00:37:10.960
and into some of the darkest
places where crime is taking

00:37:10.960 --> 00:37:14.310
place, infiltrate it
with video technology,

00:37:14.310 --> 00:37:17.410
and now the world can see
and know what's going on.

00:37:17.410 --> 00:37:21.690
And that is, you have
to know, that when

00:37:21.690 --> 00:37:25.000
you think about violent
perpetrators of horrific crime,

00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:28.950
they just seem so intimidating,
and how could you ever

00:37:28.950 --> 00:37:30.330
go against them?

00:37:30.330 --> 00:37:33.460
One of the things you have to
understand about criminality

00:37:33.460 --> 00:37:37.910
and violence is that there's
a reason why they hide it,

00:37:37.910 --> 00:37:40.180
because they're afraid.

00:37:40.180 --> 00:37:41.640
You fundamentally
hide what you're

00:37:41.640 --> 00:37:44.870
doing, because you're afraid
that if somebody saw it,

00:37:44.870 --> 00:37:48.290
you would be in trouble, and
you couldn't get away with it.

00:37:48.290 --> 00:37:51.900
And as our world has the
technology increasingly

00:37:51.900 --> 00:37:56.750
for where the bullies cannot
do this without being seen,

00:37:56.750 --> 00:37:58.460
they're going to do it less.

00:37:58.460 --> 00:38:00.044
So there's significant promise.

00:38:00.044 --> 00:38:01.710
The question now I
think, substantially,

00:38:01.710 --> 00:38:03.115
is how to get those
tools increasingly

00:38:03.115 --> 00:38:04.698
in the hands of those
who are poorest.

